<p>I have a simple singleton :</p>  <pre><code>class Error  {     private $message;     public $id;     private static $_instance;      public static function getInstance()     {         if (self::$_instance == null) {             self::$_instance = new Error();         }          return self::$_instance;     }      private function __construct()     {         $this-&gt;message = "";         $this-&gt;id= uniqid();     }  } </code></pre>  <p>I can handle the singleton within a single page but each time I refresh or I go to another page, it creates a new object.</p>  <p>I have added an ID to see what happens. When I call 3 times getInstance() in a page, I get 3 times the same object with the same ID so the singleton works. But If I refresh, I get a different ID.</p>  <p>Can you help me ?</p>